Script enables use of Raspberry Pi camera for video streaming.

Python code is created by Random Nerd Tutorials: https://randomnerdtutorials.com/video-streaming-with-raspberry-pi-camera/

I've added instalaltion of Python module prerequisite and automated the process a bit.

Commands to run:
curl -o installation.sh https://raw.githubusercontent.com/petaretjahuu/RaspberryPI/main/VideoStreaming/installation.sh
chmod +x installation.sh
sh ./installation.sh
curl -o rpi_camera_surveillance_system.py https://raw.githubusercontent.com/petaretjahuu/RaspberryPI/main/VideoStreaming/rpi_camera_surveillance_system.py

Single line command:
curl -o installation.sh https://raw.githubusercontent.com/petaretjahuu/RaspberryPI/main/VideoStreaming/installation.sh && chmod +x installation.sh && sh ./installation.sh && curl -o rpi_camera_surveillance_system.py https://raw.githubusercontent.com/petaretjahuu/RaspberryPI/main/VideoStreaming/rpi_camera_surveillance_system.py

Video streaming is started by running this command in terminal:
python3 rpi_camera_surveillance_system.py
